2020年9月3日，{{tsl|en|Capitol Police Board|国会警察委员会}}宣布自2020年9月7日起至2021年2月28日暂停公众前往[[美国国会大厦|美国国会大厦]]西翼参观，保障活动所需的就职平台、观众席及其他基础设施安全顺利搭建<ref>{{Cite press release|url=https://www.uscp.gov/media-center/press-releases/access-west-front-us-capitol-restricted-inauguration-platform|title=Access to West Front of U.S. Capitol Restricted for Inauguration Platform Construction|date=2020-09-03|publisher=United States Capitol Police|access-date=2020-01-13|archive-date=2020-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028233956/https://www.uscp.gov/media-center/press-releases/access-west-front-us-capitol-restricted-inauguration-platform|dead-url=no}}</ref>。搭建工程于2020年9月29日启动<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wusa9.com/article/news/politics/elections/inauguration-day-2021-tickets-washington-dc-expected-to-happen/65-9d89618d-dcd5-4bf2-b0ee-080b70fcb5bb|title=Inauguration Day 2021: What it will look like and what you need to know|date=2020-11-09|publisher=WUSA|access-date=2020-11-12|archive-date=2020-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201110084459/https://www.wusa9.com/article/news/politics/elections/inauguration-day-2021-tickets-washington-dc-expected-to-happen/65-9d89618d-dcd5-4bf2-b0ee-080b70fcb5bb|dead-url=no}}</ref>。标志着典礼平台搭建工程开始的“第一口钉子仪式”因[[美国最高法院|美国最高法院]][[美国最高法院大法官|大法官]]{{tsl|en|death and state funeral of Ruth Bader Ginsburg|露丝·巴德·金斯伯格的去世和葬礼}}而取消<ref>{{Cite news|last=Lesniewski|first=Niels|last2=Tully-McManus|first2=Katherine|date=2020-11-05|title=Biden or Trump, inaugural planning and construction well underway on Capitol Hill|work=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|url=https://www.post-gazette.com/news/politics-nation/2020/11/05/Biden-Trump-inaugural-planning-Capitol-Hill/stories/202011050129|dead-url=no|access-date=2020-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107163446/https://www.post-gazette.com/news/politics-nation/2020/11/05/Biden-Trump-inaugural-planning-Capitol-Hill/stories/202011050129|archive-date=2020-11-07}}</ref>。平台可容纳1600名观众<ref name=":02"/>。

==费用==
有别于过往的就职典礼，是次典礼由于观众人数大幅度减少，成本预计会下降<ref name="Inaugural-Costs2">{{Cite news|last=Fields|first=Samantha|date=2021-01-11|title=Will Capitol attack hike security costs for Biden inauguration?|publisher=Marketplace|url=https://www.marketplace.org/2021/01/11/will-capitol-attack-hike-security-costs-for-biden-inauguration/|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114194211/https://www.marketplace.org/2021/01/11/will-capitol-attack-hike-security-costs-for-biden-inauguration/|archive-date=2021-01-14}}</ref>。通常总统就职典礼的费用预计高达4490万美元，由[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿哥伦比亚特区]]承担后，再由联邦政府返还<ref name="Sept20202">{{Cite news|last=Segraves|first=Mark|date=2020-09-18|title=Why DC Officials Are Expecting Next Presidential Inauguration to Be the Most Expensive Yet|publisher=WRC-TV|url=https://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/why-dc-officials-are-expecting-next-presidential-inauguration-to-be-the-most-expensive-yet/2422371/|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107163446/https://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/why-dc-officials-are-expecting-next-presidential-inauguration-to-be-the-most-expensive-yet/2422371/|archive-date=2020-11-07}}</ref>。然而2021年国会冲击事件外加全国面临骚乱威胁，安保需求显著上升<ref name=Chalfont>{{Cite news|last=Chalfont|first=Morgan|date=2021-01-11|title=DHS secretary says security measures tied to inauguration will begin Wednesday|publisher=The Hill|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/533703-dhs-secretary-says-security-measures-tied-to-inauguration-will-begin|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114194218/https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/533703-dhs-secretary-says-security-measures-tied-to-inauguration-will-begin|archive-date=2021-01-14}}</ref>。前[[美国国土安全部|国土安全部]]官员约翰·桑德维格（John Sandweg）认为，由于[[美国总统提名大会|美国总统提名大会]]大部分改到线上举行，加上总统候选人因2019冠状病毒病疫情减少外出活动，[[美国特勤局|美国特勤局]]2020年竞选季的支出低于往年，可能有资金盈余<ref name="Inaugural-Costs2"/>。

==安保及反恐措施==
{{further|2021年冲击美国国会大厦事件}}
[[File:2021_storming_of_the_United_States_Capitol_09_(cropped).jpg|thumb]]期间占领了就职典礼平台]]
自2001年{{tsl|en|first inauguration of George W. Bush|乔治·沃克·布什第一次总统就职典礼}}以来，总统就职典礼均被列为{{tsl|en|National Special Security Event|国家特别安全事件}}；然而，今年的特别安全事件比往年早了几个星期，将准备工作纳入其中，考虑到{{tsl|en|2021 United States state capitol protests|2021年美国国会示威|连续几个星期的国会示威活动}}<ref name=":92">{{Cite news|last=Leonnig|first=Carol D.|last2=Demirjian|first2=Karoun|last3=Jouvenal|first3=Justin|last4=Miroff|first4=Nick|date=2021-01-12|title=Secret Service launches massive security operation to protect Biden inauguration|work=Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/biden-inauguration-security-dc/2021/01/12/b1a9781a-54e9-11eb-89bc-7f51ceb6bd57_story.html|dead-url=yes|access-date=2021-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125004558/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/biden-inauguration-security-dc/2021/01/12/b1a9781a-54e9-11eb-89bc-7f51ceb6bd57_story.html|archive-date=2021-01-25|issn=0190-8286}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Carney|first1=Jordain|last2=Chalfant|first2=Morgan|date=2021-01-13|title=Security concerns mount ahead of Biden inauguration|url=https://thehill.com/policy/national-security/533938-security-concerns-mount-ahead-of-biden-inauguration|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114194247/https://thehill.com/policy/national-security/533938-security-concerns-mount-ahead-of-biden-inauguration|archive-date=2021-01-14|access-date=2021-01-13|website=The Hill}}</ref>。负责为知名公职人员出席活动提供额外保安的特勤局发表声明，表示典礼会安全举行<ref name="usss-jan-8-20212">{{cite web|author1=U.S. Secret Service Communication Team|date=2021-01-08|title=Statement from the U.S. Secret Service on Inauguration Security|url=https://www.secretservice.gov/newsroom/releases/2021/01/statement-us-secret-service-inauguration-security|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114194216/https://www.secretservice.gov/newsroom/releases/2021/01/statement-us-secret-service-inauguration-security|archive-date=2021-01-14|access-date=2021-01-09|publisher=United States Secret Service}}</ref>。

冲击事件，示威者推倒了安装在就职典礼舞台工地的网状栅栏和障碍物<ref name=":92" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=Srikanth|first=Anagha|date=2021-01-14|title=Here's the lineup for President-elect Biden's inauguration ceremonies|url=https://thehill.com/changing-america/enrichment/arts-culture/534281-heres-the-lineup-for-president-elect-bidens|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114201358/https://thehill.com/changing-america/enrichment/arts-culture/534281-heres-the-lineup-for-president-elect-bidens|archive-date=2021-01-14|access-date=2021-01-14|website=TheHill}}</ref>。典礼彩排原定1月17日举行，后因安全考虑推迟至19日<ref name=":52">{{Cite web|last=Pager|first=Tyler|last2=Beavers|first2=Olivia|date=2021-01-14|title=Biden team postpones inauguration rehearsal due to security threats|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2021/01/14/biden-team-postpones-inauguration-rehearsal-due-to-security-threats-459538|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115153225/https://www.politico.com/news/2021/01/14/biden-team-postpones-inauguration-rehearsal-due-to-security-threats-459538|archive-date=2021-01-15|access-date=2021-01-15|website=POLITICO}}</ref>。拜登没有选择将典礼搬到室内举行<ref name="NewWarnings" />，表示自己“不害怕在室外宣誓就任”，表明有信心应对安全状况<ref>{{Cite web|last=Sullivan|first=Kate|date=2021-01-11|title=Biden says he is 'not afraid' of taking oath of office at US Capitol after deadly riot|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/11/politics/biden-oath-of-office-capitol/index.html|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114194242/https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/11/politics/biden-oath-of-office-capitol/index.html|archive-date=2021-01-14|access-date=2021-01-13|website=CNN}}</ref>。前{{tsl|en|Homeland Security Advisor|国土安全顾问}}{{tsl|en|Lisa Monaco|丽莎·摩纳哥}}向拜登团队提供典礼安保事宜的建议<ref name=":52" />。

示威团体及个人扬言干扰拜登就职后，特勤局启动了美国有史以来规模最大的安保行动<ref name=":92" />，竭力防止国会再度出现流血暴动<ref name=":102">{{Cite news|last=Ryan|first=Missy|last2=Horton|first2=Alex|last3=Zapotosky|first3=Matt|last4=Lamothe|first4=Dan|date=2021-01-13|title=Security footprint grows in nation’s capital ahead of inauguration-US|work=Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/2021/01/13/national-guard-inauguration-security/|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115191800/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/2021/01/13/national-guard-inauguration-security/|archive-date=2021-01-15|issn=0190-8286}}</ref>。1月11日，特朗普批准华盛顿特区宣布进入紧急状态，允许[[聯邦緊急事務管理署|聯邦緊急事務管理署]]提供联邦协助保障活动<ref>{{cite web|last=Chalfont|first=Morgan|date=2021-01-11|title=Trump approves D.C. emergency declaration ahead of Biden inauguration|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/533746-trump-makes-emergency-declaration-ahead-of-biden-inauguration?fbclid=IwAR2z5aek6cZ7FCDUJvhszL-0Ow9q9k7Stx9QualRVfYziogfjXohW5tOO9M|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114194225/https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/533746-trump-makes-emergency-declaration-ahead-of-biden-inauguration|archive-date=2021-01-14|access-date=2021-01-11|website=The Hill}}</ref>。同日，[[美国国家公园管理局|美国国家公园管理局]]警告有参与暴动的团体“继续扬言干扰”就职典礼，对“游客及公园资源构成严重威胁”<ref name=":42">{{Cite news|last=Edelman|first=Adam|date=2021-01-11|title=Biden plans 'America United' inauguration theme|agency=NBC News|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/white-house/biden-plans-america-united-inauguration-theme-n1253715|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114194313/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/white-house/biden-plans-america-united-inauguration-theme-n1253715|archive-date=2021-01-14}}</ref>。国会范围内有大量不可延展的七英尺高[[铁马_(路障)|铁马]]，防止典礼被干扰，平台遭拆解<ref>{{Cite news|last=Katkov|first=Mark|date=2021-01-07|title=Army Secretary Says A 'Non-Scalable' 7-Foot Fence Is Going Up Around U.S. Capitol|publisher=NPR|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/congress-electoral-college-tally-live-updates/2021/01/07/954469642/army-sec-says-a-temporary-fence-is-going-up-around-u-s-capitol|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108020711/https://www.npr.org/sections/congress-electoral-college-tally-live-updates/2021/01/07/954469642/army-sec-says-a-temporary-fence-is-going-up-around-u-s-capitol|archive-date=2021-01-08}}</ref>。

1月14日，联邦调查局、国土安全局及其他联邦及地方部门发表13页“威胁评估联合报告”，确认[[本土恐怖主义|本土恐怖主义]]是就职典礼最大的威胁，其次是境外[[军队政治工作学|影响行动]]和极端主义[[無人航空載具|无人机]]空袭<ref name="LevineABC">{{cite web|last=Levine|first=Mike|date=2021-01-15|title=Beyond domestic terrorists, officials eye foreign influence, drones as threats to Biden inauguration|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/domestic-terrorists-officials-eye-foreign-influence-drones-threats/story?id=75281116|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210117045053/https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/domestic-terrorists-officials-eye-foreign-influence-drones-threats/story?id=75281116|archive-date=2021-01-17|access-date=2021-01-17|website=ABC News}}</ref><ref name="NewWarnings">{{Cite news|last=Kanno-Youngs|first=Zolan|last2=Sullivan|first2=Eileen|last3=Schmitt|first3=Eric|date=2021-01-15|title=New Warnings of Violence as Security Tightens for Inauguration-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/15/us/politics/inauguration-security.html|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210117040159/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/15/us/politics/inauguration-security.html|archive-date=2021-01-17|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>。公告认为，极端分子有能力“毫无预警地展开行动，有意袭击平民和{{tsl|en|soft target|软目标}}，有能力用无需专业知识即可使用的武器造成大规模伤亡”<ref name="NewWarnings" /><ref name="LevineABC" />。另外，自1月6日国会袭击事件起，美国情报部门已发现中国、伊朗和俄罗斯意图激化紧张局面和暴力活动，与先前利用特朗普传播[[造谣|不实信息]]的尝试相呼应，手法包括发动行动质疑[[2020年美国选举邮寄投票|邮寄投票]]的安全性<ref name="NewWarnings" />。

同日，特勤局成立多部分指挥中心（Multi-Agency Command Center），协调安保事宜。指挥中心比原计划提前6天成立，抽调联邦调查局、[[美国法警|美国法警]]、[[美国国防部|国防部]]、{{le|公园警察|Park Police}}及{{le|特区地铁警察|D.C. Metro Police}}等政府机关，以及汽油公司、[[CSX运输|CSX]]铁路和[[美铁|美铁]]等私营企业共50到60个机构的代表和特工组成<ref name=":92" />。上千名全副武装的[[美国国民警卫队|国民警卫队]]从50个州、三大海外领地及哥伦比亚特区前往执勤<ref name="Troops-Capitol2">{{cite web|last=Booker|first=Brakkton|date=2021-01-13|title=About 20,000 National Guard Members To Deploy For Inauguration, Officials Say|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/congress-electoral-college-tally-live-updates/2021/01/13/956458463/20-000-national-guardsmen-will-be-deployed-for-inauguration-d-c-official-says|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114194227/https://www.npr.org/sections/insurrection-at-the-capitol/2021/01/13/956458463/20-000-national-guardsmen-will-be-deployed-for-inauguration-d-c-official-says|archive-date=2021-01-14|access-date=2021-01-13|website=NPR}}</ref><ref name=NGBJan17>{{cite press release|url=https://www.army.mil/article/242482/national_guard_troops_head_to_dc_from_as_far_away_as_guam|publisher=National Guard Bureau|title=National Guard troops head to DC from as far away as Guam|date=2021-01-17|quote=National Guard Soldiers and Airmen from all 50 states, three territories and the District of Columbia.|access-date=2021-01-18|archive-date=2021-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210118063501/https://www.army.mil/article/242482/national_guard_troops_head_to_dc_from_as_far_away_as_guam|dead-url=no}}</ref>，他们提前一个礼拜抵达，在{{tsl|en|United States Capitol Visitor Center|美国国会访客中心}}扎营<ref>{{cite web|last=Hohman|first=Maura|date=2021-01-13|title=National Guard troops seen sleeping in Capitol in striking photos|url=https://www.today.com/news/national-guard-troops-seen-sleeping-capitol-striking-photos-t205738|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114194220/https://www.today.com/news/national-guard-troops-seen-sleeping-capitol-striking-photos-t205738|archive-date=2021-01-14|access-date=2021-01-13|website=Today}}</ref>。《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》认为国会“形同临时营房，数百个警卫队员占据大理石地板，背包当枕头，没上膛的[[M4卡賓槍|M4卡賓槍]]随手可及”<ref name=":102" />。

五角大楼通过[[美国国民警卫队|美国国民警卫队]]授权最多2.1万名国民警卫队队员到白宫警戒，到1月15日将上限提升到2.5萬名<ref name=PentagonAuthorizes>Oren Liebermann, Caroline Kelly, Evan Perez and Geneva Sands, [https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/15/politics/pentagon-national-guard-inauguration/index.html Pentagon authorizes 25,000 National Guard members for inauguration] {{Wayback|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/15/politics/pentagon-national-guard-inauguration/index.html |date=20210117002655 }}, CNN (January 15, 2021).</ref>。{{tsl|en|D.C. National Guard|特区国民警卫队}}{{tsl|en|William J. Walker|威廉·J·沃克}}少将负责指挥人数在典礼前几天稳步增长的特区国民警卫队。据他估计，典礼期间被派往特区的警卫队人数在2.2万至2.5万之间<ref name=Lamothe>{{Cite news|last=Lamothe|first=Dan|date=|title=As troop levels swell in D.C., National Guard commander says he believes he has city officials' trust-US|work=Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/national-guard-dc-inauguration/2021/01/16/c46256ee-5835-11eb-89bc-7f51ceb6bd57_story.html|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-17|issn=0190-8286|archive-date=2021-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210117154209/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/national-guard-dc-inauguration/2021/01/16/c46256ee-5835-11eb-89bc-7f51ceb6bd57_story.html}}</ref>。尽管多数州长和上将侍从官愿意配合国防部要求增派人手，但仍有部分州长拒绝增派，希望留存兵力保卫自己州国会<ref name=Baldor>Lolita C. Baldor, [https://apnews.com/article/biden-inauguration-joe-biden-capitol-siege-politics-14dba91c54cd13af0aa0f3336efc1d33 Guard troops pour into Washington as states answer the call] {{Wayback|url=https://apnews.com/article/biden-inauguration-joe-biden-capitol-siege-politics-14dba91c54cd13af0aa0f3336efc1d33 |date=20210117013937 }}, Associated Press (January 17, 2021).</ref>。大批警卫队进军华盛顿也给后勤造成了困难，临近州的队员乘地面交通工具前往，偏远州队员则乘飞机前往[[安德鲁斯联合基地|安德鲁斯联合基地]]<ref name=Baldor/><ref>Luis Martinez, [https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/inside-25000-national-guardsmen-arriving-washington-dc/story?id=75299202 Inside look at how 25,000 National Guardsmen are arriving in Washington, DC: A major logistical feat was organized on short notice.] {{Wayback|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/inside-25000-national-guardsmen-arriving-washington-dc/story?id=75299202 |date=20210117064649 }}, ABC News (January 16, 2021).</ref>。美国国防官员担心这可能催生{{tsl|en|insider threat|内部威胁}}，对此陆军部长{{tsl|en|Ryan McCarthy|莱恩·麦卡锡}}确认联邦调查局将启动程序，审查驻扎特区的2.5萬名士兵。该程序会用联邦调查局的数据库和监视名单检测士兵的名字，找出与极端及恐怖组织有关或此前接受调查的红标人士<ref name=BaldorInsiderThreat>Lolita C. Baldor, [https://apnews.com/article/biden-inauguration-joe-biden-capitol-siege-ap-top-news-857bacc273e16ff82dc9fefed1242ae8 FBI vetting Guard troops in DC amid fears of insider attack] {{Wayback|url=https://apnews.com/article/biden-inauguration-joe-biden-capitol-siege-ap-top-news-857bacc273e16ff82dc9fefed1242ae8 |date=20210118041301 }}, Associated Press (January 17, 2021).</ref>。

除了保障国会安全，特区的国民警卫队还会负责{{tsl|en|traffic control|交通管制}}。警卫队[[宪兵|宪兵]]因接受处理[[内乱|内乱]]的专业训练，在此次安保工作中起到尤为重要的作用<ref name=NewWarnings/>。特区军队总人数创下美国内战以来的新高，堪比[[亚伯拉罕·林肯|亚伯拉罕·林肯]]{{tsl|en|First inauguration of Abraham Lincoln|亚伯拉罕·林肯第一次就职典礼|第一次就职典礼}}的安保级别，超过[[1968年華盛頓哥倫比亞特區大暴動|1968年華盛頓哥倫比亞特區大暴動]]所动用的1.3名国民警卫队<ref name="SchwartzUncharted">{{Cite web|last=Schwartz|first=Matthew|date=2021-01-16|title=Up To 25,000 Troops Descend On Washington For Biden's Inauguration|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/insurrection-at-the-capitol/2021/01/16/957642610/unprecedented-number-of-troops-descend-on-washington-d-c-for-bidens-inauguration|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116214956/https://www.npr.org/sections/insurrection-at-the-capitol/2021/01/16/957642610/unprecedented-number-of-troops-descend-on-washington-d-c-for-bidens-inauguration|archive-date=2021-01-16|access-date=2021-01-17|website=NPR.org}}</ref>。

应特区地铁警察的要求，美国法警会协助安保，计划从全国各地委派4000多名地方执法人员协助<ref name=":102" />。典礼前夕，[[运输安全管理局|运输安全管理局]]提升了特区地区三大机场的航空安全级别，增加随机安检门、{{tsl|en|explosive detection|爆炸物探测}}[[嗅探犬|嗅探犬]]和{{tsl|en|federal air marshal|联邦空警}}<ref name="SchwartzUncharted" /><ref name="NewWarnings" />。

