0fc23b1-4cd6-46d3-8461-cca54bc23738|archive-date=2021-01-15|access-date=2021-01-17|website=wusa9.com-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=George|first=Justin|date=2021-01-13|title=Metro to close 13 stations for a week amid threats of inauguration violence-US|work=Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/transportation/2021/01/13/metro-inauguration/|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116174312/https://www.washingtonpost.com/transportation/2021/01/13/metro-inauguration/|archive-date=2021-01-16|issn=0190-8286}}</ref>。[[美國郵政署|美國郵政署]]临时撤走或锁定公用[[邮箱|邮箱]]，暂停华盛顿及其他主要城市的收件业务<ref name="USPS2">{{Cite web|last=Moshtaghian|first=Artemis|date=2021-01-11|title=US Postal Service removing mailboxes for security reasons ahead of inauguration|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/16/us/us-postal-service-inauguration-security-mailboxes/index.html|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210117060209/https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/16/us/us-postal-service-inauguration-security-mailboxes/index.html|archive-date=2021-01-17|access-date=2021-01-16|website=CNN}}</ref>。[[爱彼迎|爱彼迎]]取消全市房间预订，各大航空公司禁止旅客携带武器登记，当地酒店行业工会呼吁限制旅客入住，国会大厦周围的许多停车场将被关闭或改道<ref>{{cite web|last=Cartagena|first=Rosa|date=2021-01-13|title=Hotel Workers’ Union Calls for DC Hotels to Close During Inauguration, but That Seems Unlikely|url=https://www.washingtonian.com/2021/01/13/hotels-inauguration-workers-union-close/|website=Washingtonian|access-date=2021-01-13|archive-date=2021-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114194327/https://www.washingtonian.com/2021/01/13/hotels-inauguration-workers-union-close/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Bowser">{{cite web|last1=Davies|first1=Emily|last2=Brice-Saddler|first2=Michael|last3=Lang|first3=Marissa|last4=Jouvenal|first4=Justin|date=2021-01-13|title=Airbnb to cancel all D.C. reservations during inauguration week as security in the city is tightened|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/airbnb-reservations-cancelled-inaugruation/2021/01/13/2205e42a-55b9-11eb-a931-5b162d0d033d_story.html|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114192245/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/airbnb-reservations-cancelled-inaugruation/2021/01/13/2205e42a-55b9-11eb-a931-5b162d0d033d_story.html|archive-date=2021-01-14|access-date=2021-01-13|website=The Washington Post}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Josephs|first=Leslie|date=2021-01-14|title=Airlines ban DC-bound travelers from checking firearms ahead of inauguration|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2021/01/14/biden-inauguration-delta-ceo-says-travelers-wont-be-allowed-to-check-firearms-into-dc.html|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115013829/https://www.cnbc.com/2021/01/14/biden-inauguration-delta-ceo-says-travelers-wont-be-allowed-to-check-firearms-into-dc.html|archive-date=2021-01-15|access-date=2021-01-15|website=CNBC}}</ref>。另外，[[馬里蘭區域通勤鐵路|馬里蘭區域通勤鐵路]]、[[維珍尼亞鐵路特快|維珍尼亞鐵路特快]]、[[美铁|美铁]][[東北區域號列車|東北區域號列車]]暂定运营<ref>{{cite news|last=Myers|first=Leah|date=2021-01-16|title=Amtrak issuing travel advisory in D.C. area for Biden’s inauguration|publisher=WTNH|location=New Haven, CT|url=https://www.wtnh.com/news/washington/washington-dc/amtrak-issuing-travel-advisory-in-d-c-area-for-bidens-inauguration/|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116205247/https://www.wtnh.com/news/washington/washington-dc/amtrak-issuing-travel-advisory-in-d-c-area-for-bidens-inauguration/|archive-date=2021-01-16}}</ref>；弗吉尼亚州在特勤局的要求下关闭[[波托马克河|波托马克河]]的四座桥梁<ref>{{Cite news|author=Reuters Staff|date=2021-01-15|title=Virginia-DC bridges to close to enhance Biden inauguration security|agency=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-biden-inauguration-bridges-idUSKBN29K2PU|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116085704/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-biden-inauguration-bridges/virginia-dc-bridges-to-close-to-enhance-biden-inauguration-security-idUSKBN29K2PU|archive-date=2021-01-16}}</ref><ref name="ARLnow">{{cite news|last=Blitz|first=Matt|date=2021-01-15|title=Four Bridges Connecting Va. to D.C. Will Be Closed Starting Tuesday|publisher=ARLnow|url=https://www.arlnow.com/2021/01/15/four-bridges-connecting-va-to-d-c-will-be-closed-starting-tuesday/|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-01-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116200436/https://www.arlnow.com/2021/01/15/four-bridges-connecting-va-to-d-c-will-be-closed-starting-tuesday/|archive-date=2021-01-16}}</ref>。[[安飛士·百捷集團|安飛士·百捷集團]]、[[赫茲租車|赫茲租車]]、[[萬豪國際|萬豪國際]]和[[凱悅酒店|凱悅酒店]]应{{tsl|en|House Oversight Committee|众议院监督委员会}}要求，加强旅客安检<ref name=":52"/>。

===安全事件===
1月15日，国会警察逮捕[[弗兰特罗亚尔_(弗吉尼亚州)|弗兰特罗亚尔]]籍的31岁男子。该男子携带“非经授权”的就职典礼通行证，打算进入国会范围的限制区域。警方在他的[[福特F系列|福特F-150]]卡车中发现一把装有{{tsl|en|high-capacity magazine|高容量弹匣}}并上膛的[[格洛克手枪|格洛克手枪]]、500多发弹药（包括[[中空弹|中空弹]]）及20发霰弹枪子弹<ref name=":11">{{Cite news|last=Contrera|first=Jessica|last2=Leonnig|first2=Carol D.|last3=Mettler|first3=Katie|date=2021-01-16|title=Va. man arrested at inauguration checkpoint says he was lost and didn’t mean to bring gun, ammunition to D.C.-US|work=Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/beeler-arrest-inauguration-checkpoint/2021/01/16/8597db24-5834-11eb-a817-e5e7f8a406d6_story.html|dead-url=yes|access-date=2021-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122230552/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/beeler-arrest-inauguration-checkpoint/2021/01/16/8597db24-5834-11eb-a817-e5e7f8a406d6_story.html|archive-date=2021-01-22|issn=0190-8286}}</ref>。男子身份为私人保镖，协助市区的安保工作。他承认持有上膛手枪和霰弹枪子弹，但否认故意带着500发子弹开车，又表示自己开车来华盛顿前忘记车上有武器，自己在城里迷了路，只好使用他拿到的通行证<ref name=":11" />。该男子被控无证持有手枪、持有未登记武器和弹药。《华盛顿邮报》表示该男子和极端组织无关，非常配合警方<ref name=":11" />。

1月17日，弗吉尼亚州{{tsl|en|Gordonsville, Virginia|戈登斯维尔 (弗吉尼亚州)|戈登斯维尔}}一名报称特朗普支持者的22岁男子在国会被捕。他持有一把[[格洛克手枪|格洛克22]]手枪、三枚高容量弹匣和37发未登记子弹<ref name="ManWoman">{{Cite web|last=Meckler|first=Laura|date=2021-01-17|title=Avowed Trump supporter arrested near Capitol for carrying gun; women charged with impersonating police|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/public-safety/capitol-security-zone-arrests/2021/01/17/41c60318-58e2-11eb-a976-bad6431e03e2_story.html|dead-url=yes|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124153753/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/public-safety/capitol-security-zone-arrests/2021/01/17/41c60318-58e2-11eb-a976-bad6431e03e2_story.html|archive-date=2021-01-24|access-date=2021-01-18|website=Washington Post}}</ref>。同日，[[康涅狄格州|康涅狄格州]][[斯特拉特福德_(康乃狄克州)|斯特拉特福德]]一名63岁女子自称执法人员兼总统内阁成员，在一处检查站附近被国会警察截查，但她随即逃跑，最终接受精神病检查并被逮捕，遭控{{tsl|en|Police impersonation|假冒警察}}、拒绝遵守交通要求和逃避警察<ref>[https://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/woman-arrested-at-inauguration-checkpoint-said-she-was-officer-cabinet-member-police/2544325/ Woman Arrested at Inauguration Checkpoint Said She Was Officer, Cabinet Member: Police] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/woman-arrested-at-inauguration-checkpoint-said-she-was-officer-cabinet-member-police/2544325/ |date=20210118155239 }}, NBC Washington (January 17, 2021).</ref><ref name=ManWoman/>。也是在同一天，[[新墨西哥州|新墨西哥州]][[奧特羅縣_(新墨西哥州)|奥特罗县]]县委员、“牛仔为特朗普”（Cowboys for Trump）组织创办人库伊·格里芬（Couy Griffin）在华盛顿被捕，他被控参与1月6日国会暴动，扬言在就职典礼当天再度持枪在国会举行集会，为国会“流血到死”<ref>Associated Press/NBC Washington, [https://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/new-mexico-county-commissioner-arrested-in-dc-for-involvement-in-capitol-riot/2544645/ New Mexico County Commissioner Arrested in DC for Involvement in Capitol Riot] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/new-mexico-county-commissioner-arrested-in-dc-for-involvement-in-capitol-riot/2544645/ |date=20210118130643 }} (January 17, 2021).</ref>。

